{"type":"message","id":"6e512c83","parentId":"8664e3d1","timestamp":"2026-03-01T09:00:06.709Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_bfa1aadc401a4629be6893dc","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"AI IoT devices market trends 2026 ESP32 consumer products\",\n  \"provider\": \"brave\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 1785,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"brave\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"21a8679d6fe9cae7\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nTop 10 ESP32 IoT Projects You Can Build in 2026\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"21a8679d6fe9cae7\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://iotbeat.com/blog/top-10-esp32-iot-projects-you-can-build-in-2026\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"534f91549c6d4df1\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nDiscover the top 10 ESP32 IoT projects to build in 2026, including <strong>smart home automation and voice control systems</strong>.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"534f91549c6d4df1\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"1 week ago\",\n      \"siteName\": \"iotbeat.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"44b9a033b7146450\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nWireless IoT Chip Market Poised to Triple to $26.3 Billion by 2031: The Semiconductor Backbone of the 50-Billion-Device Era\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"44b9a033b7146450\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.openpr.com/news/4408348/wireless-iot-chip-market-poised-to-triple-to-26-3-billion\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b1d54ad1711459d5\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThe Multi-Protocol Trend: The most significant strategic development is the rise of chips that natively support multiple protocols (e.g., a single chip supporting Bluetooth, Zigbee, and Thread). This allows device makers to build a single hardware platform that can address multiple market segments and future-proof their products against protocol evolution. Companies like Espressif Systems, with its popular ESP32 series, have pioneered this approach, democratizing access to advanced connectivity.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"b1d54ad1711459d5\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"1 day ago\",\n      \"siteName\": \"www.openpr.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5fbed51d9e2d0e88\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nLeading IoT Gateways for Smart Homes in 2026\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5fbed51d9e2d0e88\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://iotbeat.com/blog/comparing-the-leading-iot-gateways-for-smart-homes-in-2026\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d4a8d289f3810664\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nExplore the top 10 ESP32 IoT projects for 2026, featuring <strong>smart home automation, voice control, and energy monitoring</strong>.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d4a8d289f3810664\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"1 week ago\",\n      \"siteName\": \"iotbeat.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"466a9582e012e7ed\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nInside IoT Now Q1 2026: AI, SGP.32 and the Future of Connectivity | IoT Now News & Reports\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"466a9582e012e7ed\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.iot-now.com/2026/02/24/155434-inside-iot-now-q1-2026-ai-sgp-32-and-the-future-of-connectivity/\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3eea974b1fa94bee\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n... A practical guide from ... strategy. ... <strong>Aeris surpasses 100 million connections, Telenor IoT passes 30 million units, and AT&amp;T launches its first end-to-end IoT solution on AWS Marketplace</strong>....\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_