ort, Hat expansion header, and SDIO/ISP expansion interfaces, making it suitable for industrial HMI panels, PoE smart terminals, camera/vision acquisition nodes, smart home controllers, and edge computing devices. ... Dual-core 32-bit RISC-V HP (High-performance) CPU @ up to 400 MHz with AI instructions extension and single-precision FPU · Single-RISC-V LP (Low-power) MCU c\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d11d0f1ec5136742\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"1 day ago\",\n      \"siteName\": \"www.cnx-software.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3d4eec3bfbbef18b\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThe Ultimate HMI: Unleashing the ESP32-P4 10-inch AI Display\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3d4eec3bfbbef18b\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.elecrow.com/blog/esp32-p4-10-inch-ai-display-guide.html\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"edf2a621c47328c0\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nDiscover how the ESP32-P4’s RISC-V dual-core power, MIPI-DSI interface, and hardware accelerators revolutionize 10.1&quot; AI displays for edge computing and smooth HMI.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"edf2a621c47328c0\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"1 month ago\",\n      \"siteName\": \"www.elecrow.com\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"ESP32-P4 AI capabilities edge computing consumer applications","provider":"brave","count":5,"tookMs":1710,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"brave","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"ace8932fbfe968ab\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nBigger, Faster, Better: The ESP32-P4-WIFI6 HMI is Here - Hackster.io\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"ace8932fbfe968ab\">>>","url":"https://www.hackster.io/news/bigger-faster-better-the-esp32-p4-wifi6-hmi-is-here-d088fda7f0c0","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"92300a27a7bec0df\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nAudio capabilities are handled ... The ESP32-P4 includes <strong>secure boot, flash encryption, cryptographic accelerators, a true random number generator, and hardware access protection mechanisms</strong>....\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"92300a27a7bec0df\">>>","published":"17 hours ago","siteName":"www.hackster.io"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"7d4ab7624ec3f624\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nAI Assistant Uses ESP32 | Hackaday\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"7d4ab7624ec3f624\">>>","url":"https://hackaday.com/2026/02/27/ai-assistant-uses-esp32/","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"836f4d8b552b7c2a\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nHaving an AI assistant is all the rage these days, but AI assistants usually don’t know about your automation setups and may have difficulty dealing with tasks asynchronously. Enter zclaw. It gives you the option to have a personal assistant on an ESP32 backed by Anthropic, OpenAI, or OpenRouter.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"836f4d8b552b7c2a\">>>","published":"2 days ago","siteName":"hackaday.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"577a84480a8e7fec\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nM5Stack’s Newest PoE-Enabled ESP32-P4 Module Is Available - Hackster.io\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"577a84480a8e7fec\">>>","url":"https://www.hackster.io/news/m5stack-s-newest-poe-enabled-esp32-p4-module-is-available-a3d18bd9d010","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"6c2d00228903196a\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nThe SoC includes <strong>AI instruction extensions and a single-precision FPU</strong>, giving it considerably more headroom than earlier ESP-class parts when handling graphics pipelines, signal processing, or lightweight machine vision workloads.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"6c2d00228903196a\">>>","published":"5 hours ago","siteName":"www.hackster.io"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"67616d268227914a\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nM5Stack Unit PoE-P4 - A tiny PoE-powered ESP32-P4 development kit with MIPI DSI/CSI and USB-C connectors - CNX Software\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"67616d268227914a\">>>","url":"https://www.cnx-software.com/2026/02/27/m5stack-unit-poe-p4-a-tiny-poe-powered-esp32-p4-development-kit-with-mipi-dsi-csi-and-usb-c-connectors/","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d11d0f1ec5136742\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nIt’s designed as a network-enabled node with built-in PoE (up to 6W output), a USB Type-C host port, and a separate USB Type-C OTG/download interface, along with an RGB LED, IR transmitter, user button, Grove (HY2.0-4P) port, Hat expansion header, and SDIO/ISP expansion interfaces, making it suitable for industrial HMI panels, PoE smart terminals, camera/vision acquisition nodes, smart home controllers, and edge computing devices. ... Dual-core 32-bit RISC-V HP (High-performance) CPU @ up to 400 MHz with AI instructions extension and single-precision FPU · Single-RISC-V LP (Low-power) MCU c\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d11d0f1ec5136742\">>>","published":"1 day ago","siteName":"www.cnx-software.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"3d4eec3bfbbef18b\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nThe Ultimate HMI: Unleashing the ESP32-P4 10-inch AI Display\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"3d4eec3bfbbef18b\">>>","url":"https://www.elecrow.com/blog/esp32-p4-10-inch-ai-display-guide.html","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"edf2a621c47328c0\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nDiscover how the ESP32-P4’s RISC-V dual-core power, MIPI-DSI interface, and hardware accelerators revolutionize 10.1&quot; AI displays for edge computing and smooth HMI.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"edf2a621c47328c0\">>>","published":"1 month ago","siteName":"www.elecrow.com"}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772355657699}}
