hese days, but AI assistants usually don’t know about your automation setups and may have difficulty dealing with tasks asynchronously. Enter zclaw. It gives you the option to have a personal assistant on an ESP32 backed by Anthropic, OpenAI, or OpenRouter.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d134b1bd8a69ec3b\">>>","published":"2 days ago","siteName":"hackaday.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"b95f50c1ab0cc5e7\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nESP32 - Wikipedia\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"b95f50c1ab0cc5e7\">>>","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ESP32","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"2720965dbb306677\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nESP32 is a family of low-cost, energy-efficient microcontrollers that <strong>integrate both Wi-Fi and Bluetooth capabilities</strong>. These chips feature a variety of processing options, including the Tensilica Xtensa LX6 microprocessor available in both dual-core ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"2720965dbb306677\">>>","published":"1 week ago","siteName":"en.wikipedia.org"}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772355711351}}
